column153: I have been randomly seeing two brown anoles in my backyard sunning themselves on my grill during the day during this summer 2012. As the weather is getting colder they are sunning themselves more often on my grill. One is very large and dark color (~7-8 inches head to tail) the other is smaller (~5-6 inches head to tail). With there appearance the green anoles have been very hard to find. As well as the skinks.
